Setup on server

cd ~/my_nemotron
unzip floodiq-code.zip -d .
mkdir -p floodiq/data/raw
unzip floodiq-data.zip -d floodiq/data/raw
cd floodiq
source ~/nemotron/venv/bin/activate
python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
Verify required raw files

ls -lah data/raw
Must include:

be_NYC_004.tif, be_NYC_005.tif, be_NYC_008.tif, be_NYC_009.tif
building_footprints.json
311_flooding_bronx.json, 311_ida_bronx.json
ms4_outfalls.zip (shapefile zip preferred)
landcover_2021.tif
fvi_scores.json (placeholder or real)
Preprocess (strict Open Data mode)

python data/data_loader.py --preprocess --strict-open-data
Run backend

python scripts/precompute_scenarios.py
uvicorn api.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8001
Run frontend (new terminal)

cd ~/my_nemotron/floodiq/frontend
npm install
npm run dev -- --host 0.0.0.0 --port 5173
Open in browser

